again, and I'm starving.

119
00:08:51,988 --> 00:08:54,221
Make something to eat.

120
00:08:54,254 --> 00:08:55,488
-Yeah, dream on.

121
00:08:55,521 --> 00:08:57,388
You'll starve to death waiting
for me to cook for you.

122
00:08:57,421 --> 00:09:00,188
And even if I did cook a meal,
I wouldn't let you have any.

123
00:09:00,221 --> 00:09:01,621
Dumb ass.

124
00:09:01,654 --> 00:09:02,954
-Hey, Love.

125
00:09:02,988 --> 00:09:04,988
Have you heard that new song
from the Prince of Darkness

126
00:09:05,021 --> 00:09:06,054
that just came out?

127
00:09:06,088 --> 00:09:07,688
It totally rocks.

128
00:09:07,721 --> 00:09:10,754
-No, but have you read
the latest issue of

129
00:09:10,788 --> 00:09:12,088
Shonen Jump magazine?

130
00:09:12,121 --> 00:09:13,054
-How could I?

131
00:09:13,088 --> 00:09:14,954
You never let anyone
read it but you.

132
00:09:14,988 --> 00:09:17,954
-Hysterical!

133
00:09:17,988 --> 00:09:21,621
-Lisa, I want you to keep a
sharp eye on that Soul Reaper

134
00:09:21,654 --> 00:09:22,754
and look after him.

135
00:09:22,788 --> 00:09:24,721
-Don't worry, I won't
let him out of my sight.

136
00:09:24,754 --> 00:09:26,388
-Yeah, but you're
not watching him.

137
00:09:26,421 --> 00:09:29,121
You're just sitting there,
looking at swimsuit catalogs.

138
00:09:29,154 --> 00:09:29,954
-Can it.

139
00:09:29,988 --> 00:09:32,054
I can see the Soul Reaper fine.

140
00:09:32,088 --> 00:09:33,388
-That's not the point.

141
00:09:33,421 --> 00:09:34,788
You're on duty
today, aren't you?

142
00:09:34,821 --> 00:09:36,621
You're supposed to
be training him.

143
00:09:36,654 --> 00:09:38,588
-Fine, have it your way.

144
00:09:38,621 --> 00:09:40,054
One, two.

145
00:09:40,088 --> 00:09:41,454
One, two.

146
00:09:41,488 --> 00:09:42,754
One, two.

147
00:09:42,788 --> 00:09:43,388
One, two.

148
00:09:43,421 --> 00:09:44,288
-It sure is late.

149
00:09:44,321 --> 00:09:45,621
-Stop talking about it.

150
00:09:45,654 --> 00:09:49,088
You're already making us more
hungry than we already are.

151
00:09:49,121 --> 00:09:49,654
-One, two.

152
00:09:49,688 --> 00:09:50,621
One, two.

153
00:09:50,654 --> 00:09:52,554
One, two.

154
00:09:52,588 --> 00:09:54,021
One, two.

155
00:09:54,054 --> 00:09:55,988
One--

156
00:09:56,021 --> 00:09:59,221
-I can't take it anymore!

157
00:09:59,254 --> 00:10:00,588
-What's the idea?

158
00:10:00,621 --> 00:10:02,688
You try something like
that again, dumb ass,

159
00:10:02,721 --> 00:10:03,788
and you're dead!

160
00:10:03,821 --> 00:10:06,221
-I was, I was just going
to say that to him.

161
00:10:06,254 --> 00:10:08,654
-I should be saying that to you!

162
00:10:08,688 --> 00:10:11,121
You bragged about how you were
going to teach me control,

163
00:10:11,154 --> 00:10:13,188
and how to suppress the
Hollow inside me forever.

164
00:10:13,221 --> 00:10:16,621
So why the hell are you idiots
making me run all day long

165
00:10:16,654 --> 00:10:19,088
on this cheap, homemade, poor
excuse for a cross country ski

166
00:10:19,121 --> 00:10:20,388
machine?

167
00:10:20,421 --> 00:10:22,121
Wait, scratch that.

168
00:10:22,154 --> 00:10:23,121
You're not the idiots.

169
00:10:23,154 --> 00:10:24,921
I'm the idiot for
listening to you.

170
00:10:24,954 --> 00:10:27,188
-You are an idiot if you
think it's a cross-country ski

171
00:10:27,221 --> 00:10:28,688
machine!

172
00:10:28,721 --> 00:10:29,621
-Lunch is here!

173
00:10:29,654 --> 00:10:31,888
-Ah, sounds good.

174
