consider this training?

178
00:10:38,988 --> 00:10:41,421
-I'll call you dumb ass
any time I want, dumbass.

179
00:10:41,454 --> 00:10:43,588
-Should I interrupt them
to tell them lunch is here?

180
00:10:43,621 --> 00:10:44,421
It might get cold.

181
00:10:44,454 --> 00:10:46,121
-Ah, don't bother.

182
00:10:46,154 --> 00:10:48,521
I'll eat theirs.

183
00:10:48,554 --> 00:10:49,988
-They seem to be awfullly angry.

184
00:10:50,021 --> 00:10:52,854
Why are they fighting?

185
00:10:52,888 --> 00:10:56,821
-Well, he doesn't seem to
like the Hiyori super-trainer?

186
00:10:56,854 --> 00:10:57,488
-What?

187
00:10:57,521 --> 00:11:00,888
He was still on it?

188
00:11:00,921 --> 00:11:03,121
-If you ask me, I don't
think Hiyori explained

189
00:11:03,154 --> 00:11:05,388
the theory of the
training treadmill

190
00:11:05,421 --> 00:11:07,854
very well, so I can see why
the Soul Reaper might be upset.

191
00:11:16,221 --> 00:11:17,354
-I have to agree.

192
00:11:17,388 --> 00:11:19,754
When giving orders,
she always leaves

193
00:11:19,788 --> 00:11:21,954
out one or two key details.

194
00:11:21,988 --> 00:11:22,454
-Hm.

195
00:11:26,354 --> 00:11:29,254
-Quit complaining, and keep
running until you drop!

196
00:11:34,188 --> 00:11:34,654
-Why you!

197
00:11:38,121 --> 00:11:39,988
-Calm down, Ichigo.

198
00:11:40,021 --> 00:11:42,121
The stupid Hiyori
treadmill trainer--

199
00:11:42,154 --> 00:11:43,221
-It's super!

200
00:11:43,254 --> 00:11:45,454
---is foundation for
your future training.

201
00:11:45,488 --> 00:11:46,788
-Foundation?

202
00:11:46,821 --> 00:11:49,254
-We determine the level of
your next training program

203
00:11:49,288 --> 00:11:52,721
based on how long you
can run on the treadmill.

204
00:11:52,754 --> 00:11:56,221
-What exactly do you
mean, when you say level?

205
00:11:56,254 --> 00:11:58,354
-Just listen to Hiyori, OK?

206
00:11:58,388 --> 00:11:59,821
Quit complaining,
and get back on

207
00:11:59,854 --> 00:12:01,788
her senseless treadmill trainer.

208
00:12:01,821 --> 00:12:04,754
-For the last time, it's the
Hiyori Super Trainer, dumb ass.

209
00:12:04,788 --> 00:12:08,188
-After about three days, you'll
collapse from exhaustion.

210
00:12:08,221 --> 00:12:10,754
First we break you down,
and then we build you up,

211
00:12:10,788 --> 00:12:14,388
by teaching you how to control
your Hollow transformation.

212
00:12:14,421 --> 00:12:15,121
-What?

213
00:12:15,154 --> 00:12:16,621
That's a joke.

214
00:12:16,654 --> 00:12:18,688
Well you can forget
about three days.

215
00:12:18,721 --> 00:12:20,454
I can run on that
thing for almost a week

216
00:12:20,488 --> 00:12:21,921
without getting tired.

217
00:12:21,954 --> 00:12:23,621
I get it, OK?

218
00:12:23,654 --> 00:12:25,854
That stupid machine is
designed to drain me

219
00:12:25,888 --> 00:12:27,488
of all my spirit energy.

220
00:12:27,521 --> 00:12:29,921
Well big deal!

221
00:12:29,954 --> 00:12:32,388
You want to measure my
maximum spirit energy output

222
00:12:32,421 --> 00:12:37,088
by seeing how many days I
can run before I collapse.

223
00:12:37,121 --> 00:12:38,154
You idiots.

224
00:12:38,188 --> 00:12:39,588
With the spirit energy
I have right now,

225
00:12:39,621 --> 00:12:42,021
I can go at least five days
straight on that thing!

226
00:12:42,054 --> 00:12:44,421
There's no point in
testing me like this.

227
00:12:44,454 --> 00:12:47,721
Just teach me how to control
my Hollowfication, already!

228
00:12:47,754 --> 00:12:50,288
I don't have time to waste
on this crap, damn it!

229
00:12:50,321 --> 00:12:53,288
I cannot afford to lose any more
time playing around with you

230
00:12:53,321 --> 00:12:54,121
Visords!

231
00:12:54,154 --> 00:12:54,854
-Shut your mouth!

232
00:13:05,754 --> 00:13:07,421
You don't have time?

233
00:13:07,454 --> 00:13:08,854
Oh, that's really
something, coming

234
00:13:08,888 --> 00:13:10,854
from a guy who doesn't
even know how long it

235
00:13:10,888 --> 00:13:12,488
takes for the Hogyoku to awaken.

236
00:13:15,021 --> 00:13:15,688
-Wait a minute.

237
00:13:15,721 --> 00:13:18,588
What did you just say?

238
00:13:18,621 --> 00:13:20,454
-I said, stop blabbing,
when you don't really

239
00:13:20,488 --> 00:13:22,288
know anything about
the Hogyoku or anything

240
00:13:22,321 --> 00:13:23,454
at all about Hollowfication.

241
00:13:25,888 --> 00:13:26,554
-What is this?

242
00:13:26,588 --> 00:13:27,788
How do you know about?

243
00:13:27,821 --> 00:13:30,688
How is it possible you
know about the Hogyoku?

244
00:13:30,721 --> 00:13:33,121
-I know all about it.

245
00:13:33,154 --> 00:13:38,988
The Hogyoku, the Arrancars,
even Sosuke Aizen.

246
00:13:39,021 --> 00:13:42,121
I've known all about them
for many, many years.

247
00:13:49,221 --> 00:13:52,621
Don't worry, I'll give you
all the details another day.

248
00:13:52,654 --> 00:13:54,188
I thought it would
be a good idea

249
00:13:54,221 --> 00:13:56,721
to take some time
at the beginning,

250
00:13:56,754 --> 00:13:58,921
so you can get used to us.

251
00:13:58,954 --> 00:14:01,688
But, now that I
think about it, you

252
00:14:01,721 --> 00:14:04,388
can already turn
into a Soul Reaper.

253
00:14:04,421 --> 00:14:07,654
You can use your Shikai.

254
00:14:07,688 --> 00:14:11,554
And you have a Bankai.

255
00:14:11,588 --> 00:14:14,688
-You know about all that, too?

256
00:14:14,721 --> 00:14:17,421
-But I can see it would be
better if we just jumped right

257
00:14:17,454 --> 00:14:20,321
into teaching you how
to control your Hollow.

258
00:14:20,354 --> 00:14:22,288
Just like you
originally asked us to.

259
00:14:22,321 --> 00:14:23,654
Are you ready, Ichigo?

260
00:14:29,454 --> 00:14:31,721
I hope you don't regret this.

261
00:14:38,221 --> 00:14:41,888
Hachi, give us a two-layered
fault force field.

262
00:14:41,921 --> 00:14:43,121
-All right, then.

263
00:15:02,621 --> 00:15:05,388
-Can you hear me, Ichigo?

264
00:15:05,421 --> 00:15:09,121
In a moment, you're going to
fully transform into a Hollow.

265
00:15:09,154 --> 00:15:11,788
Don't let it consume you.

266
00:15:11,821 --> 00:15:13,888
Consume it, instead.

267
00:15:13,921 --> 00:15:17,654
If it eats you, it's all over.

268
00:15:31,488 --> 00:15:32,688
Hey Hachi.

269
00:15:32,721 --> 00:15:34,654
Throw up a force
field here, too.

270
00:15:34,688 --> 00:15:35,854
-Whaaat?

271
00:15:35,888 --> 00:15:36,754
-Don't whaaat?

272
00:15:36,788 --> 00:15:37,888
Me.

273
00:15:37,921 --> 00:15:39,054
You're standing there
with your mouth open,

274
00:15:39,088 --> 00:15:41,988
looking like you're
trying to catch flies.

275
00:15:42,021 --> 00:15:43,921
Just do it, OK?

276
00:15:43,954 --> 00:15:46,588
And seal off Ichigo's
body as well.

277
00:15:46,621 --> 00:15:47,121
-As you wish.

278
00:15:53,321 --> 00:15:54,854
Wall of iron sand.

279
00:15:54,888 --> 00:15:56,988
Tower of the Shaven Priests.

280
00:15:57,021 --> 00:16:00,154
Glow incandescent iron,
tranquil and soundless.

281
00:16:04,921 --> 00:16:07,121
Bakudo #75.

282
00:16:07,154 --> 00:16:08,621
Gochutekkan!

283
00:16:08,654 --> 00:16:09,621
[music playing]

284
00:16:29,954 --> 00:16:30,921
[wind]

285
00:16:44,354 --> 00:16:45,021
-Hey!

286
00:16:45,054 --> 00:16:48,521
Long time, no see, King.

287
00:16:48,554 --> 00:16:50,788
What's wrong?

288
00:16:50,821 --> 00:16:55,654
By the expression on
your face you look glum.

289
00:16:55,688 --> 00:16:57,121
[music playing]

290
00:17:06,788 --> 00:17:09,088
-Where the hell is Zangetsu?

291
00:17:09,121 --> 00:17:11,521
Answer me.

292
00:17:11,554 --> 00:17:13,421
I want to know now, dammit!

293
00:17:13,454 --> 00:17:15,254
-I'm confused.

294
00:17:15,288 --> 00:17:17,988
When you talk about
Zangetsu, do you

295
00:17:18,021 --> 00:17:21,521
mean the one you're
holding, in your hand?

296
00:17:21,554 --> 00:17:23,421
Or is it this one, in mine?

297
00:17:26,254 --> 00:17:27,254
Beautiful, isn't it?

298
00:17:31,954 --> 00:17:35,321
-A white Zangetsu?

299
00:17:35,354 --> 00:17:37,054
-You asked me a question.

300
00:17:37,088 --> 00:17:39,021
Where's Zangetsu?

301
00:17:39,054 --> 00:17:40,121
Well here's your answer.

302
00:17:43,488 --> 00:17:44,854
I am Zangetsu!

303
00:17:49,921 --> 00:17:50,854
[music playing]

304
00:17:58,169 --> 00:18:01,069
[explosion]

305
00:18:01,102 --> 00:18:04,535
[rumbling]

306
00:18:06,230 --> 00:18:07,130
-Here it comes.

307
00:18:10,663 --> 00:18:13,396
-You think maybe it
would be a good idea

308
00:18:13,430 --> 00:18:15,263
if we hid his Zanpakuto?

309
00:18:15,296 --> 00:18:16,696
-Wouldn't make any difference.

310
00:18:16,730 --> 00:18:20,330
If he couldn't find it, it would
just make him more frantic.

311
00:18:20,363 --> 00:18:21,330
[music playing]

312
00:18:45,630 --> 00:18:46,263
-Hachigen.

313
00:18:46,296 --> 00:18:48,196
Open it up, please.

314
00:18:48,230 --> 00:18:51,963
I'm the one on duty today,
so I'll be going first.

315
00:18:51,996 --> 00:18:52,696
-All right, Lisa.

316
00:18:59,630 --> 00:19:03,063
-Let's try not to
kill him, Lisa.

317
00:19:03,096 --> 00:19:05,796
-Yeah, if he doesn't
kill me, first.

318
00:19:05,830 --> 00:19:06,796
[music playing]

319
00:19:19,730 --> 00:19:21,730
My name is Lisa Yadomaru.

320
00:19:24,696 --> 00:19:25,630
Nice to meet you.

321
00:19:36,363 --> 00:19:37,596
-Say it!

322
00:19:37,630 --> 00:19:40,663
Why won't you tell me
what happened to Zangetsu?

323
00:19:40,696 --> 00:19:43,630
-You're persistent,
making me repeat myself.

324
00:19:43,663 --> 00:19:46,196
I told you, I'm Zangetsu!

325
00:19:49,196 --> 00:19:50,163
[explosion]

326
00:19:54,696 --> 00:19:55,496
-Ichigo.

327
00:19:55,530 --> 00:19:58,063
Maybe you aren't aware of this.

328
00:19:58,096 --> 00:20:01,096
But Zangetsu and I have
always been one and the same.

329
00:20:03,763 --> 00:20:05,563
Together we're
your spirit energy.

330
00:20:05,596 --> 00:20:07,996
I used to be part of him.

331
00:20:08,030 --> 00:20:09,596
We share the same body.

332
00:20:15,963 --> 00:20:18,763
But, as our relationship
began to change,

333
00:20:18,796 --> 00:20:21,596
so too, did our
individual appearances.

334
00:20:21,630 --> 00:20:24,230
When life is in control,
flesh covers the bones.

335
00:20:24,263 --> 00:20:28,796
When death takes over,
the bones become exposed.

336
00:20:28,830 --> 00:20:31,763
It's the same with
Zangetsu and I.

337
00:20:31,796 --> 00:20:33,396
Over time, my power increased.

338
00:20:33,430 --> 00:20:35,896
Control started to
switch over to death,

339
00:20:35,930 --> 00:20:39,663
and Zangetsu became
a part of me.

340
00:20:39,696 --> 00:20:42,896
The more you try draw
on Zangetsu's powers,

341
00:20:42,930 --> 00:20:46,996
the easier it became for
me to dominate your soul.

342
00:20:52,130 --> 00:20:55,296
-Is that so?

343
00:20:55,330 --> 00:20:59,696
Then that means, if
I defeat you here,

344
00:20:59,730 --> 00:21:01,263
then Zangetsu will
once again become

345
00:21:01,296 --> 00:21:04,696
the center of my spirit energy.

346
00:21:04,730 --> 00:21:08,063
-That makes sense.

347
00:21:08,096 --> 00:21:08,563
In theory.

348
00:21:11,430 --> 00:21:14,830
But you won't win.

349
00:21:14,863 --> 00:21:15,463
-Is that right?

350
00:21:24,663 --> 00:21:26,130
Don't be so sure about that.

351
00:21:26,163 --> 00:21:30,896
I wonder how confident you'll
be, after you see this!

352
00:21:30,930 --> 00:21:34,396
-You just don't
understand, do you?

353
00:21:34,430 --> 00:21:36,763
It's not like you might beat me.

354
00:21:36,796 --> 00:21:39,763
You can't beat me!

355
00:21:39,796 --> 00:21:40,763
[music playing]

356
00:22:03,730 --> 00:22:04,196
-Bankai!

357
00:22:13,464 --> 00:22:13,964
[theme music]

358
00:23:43,739 --> 00:23:45,439
-You there, in front of the TV!

359
00:23:45,473 --> 00:23:46,839
Need some exercise?

360
00:23:46,873 --> 00:23:50,373
Now the Hiyori Super Trainer can
be yours, for a low, low price.

361
00:23:50,406 --> 00:23:52,806
Buy it now, and get it
signed by Hiyori Sarugaki.

362
00:23:52,839 --> 00:23:55,106
-Wait, didn't you break it
when you threw it at Ichigo?

363
00:23:55,139 --> 00:23:55,939
-Quiet, dumbass.

364
00:23:55,973 --> 00:23:58,506
You're blowing my sales pitch.

